The first one I presented is the way the Moose documentation calls has, the way the Moose test suite typically calls has, and the way I and most of the rest of the Moose Cabal call has.<p>The second one isn&#x27;t common at all, but I have seen people both completely leave out the parentheses:<p><pre><code>    has foo => is => &#x27;ro&#x27;, isa => &#x27;Str&#x27;, ...;
</code></pre>
or treat has as a straight function<p><pre><code>    has(foo, is => &#x27;ro&#x27;, isa => &#x27;Str&#x27;);
</code></pre>
both of which cause Perl::Tidy to do weird things.
